label: A3B_hP24_194_hk_bf-001
title: VCo$_{3}$ Structure
comments:
(Saito, 1959) states that this is the hexagonal analog of the \href{current_web_home_dir/AB3_cP4_221_a_c-001}{cubic Cu$_{3}$Au ($L1_{2}$) structure}.  He placed it in space group $P\overline{6}m2$ \#187, but (Cenzual, 1991) showed that the given structure actually is in space group $P6_{3}/mmc$ \#194. 
 VCo$_{3}$ and \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_hP24_194_hk_bf-002}{hexagonal PuAl$_{3}$} have the same AFLOW prototype label, A3B\_hP24\_194\_hk\_bf.  They are generated by the same symmetry operations with different sets of parameters ({\tt --params}) specified in their corresponding CIF files.
